The Second Amendment concerns the right "- - to keep and bear arms."

The National Rifle Association leads the pro-gun lobby and strictly
interprets the Amendment without controls.

Gun control advocates interpret the Amendment according to its 1792
context and see the need for controls.

Public opinion appears to favor gun controls.</SUM>
